## Functions

### isValidIDChar() {#a83884a0d8fa84acdbd02874c7994b881}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="static bool isValidIDChar (char C, bool First)"
  labels = {["static"]}>
Returns true if <code>C</code> is a valid character in an identifier.

If <code>First</code> is true, returns true if <code>C</code> is a valid first character of an identifier, else returns true if <code>C</code> is a valid non-first character of an identifier. Identifiers match the following regular expression: &#91;a-zA-Z&#95;&#93;&#91;0-9a-zA-Z&#95;&#93;&#42;
